Wars & Indepence
Declaration of Independence
Date: July 4, 1776
The Second Continental Congress officially adopted this document, declaring independence from Great Britain.
Territorial Acquisitions
Louisiana Purchase
Date: April 30, 1803
The United States acquired approximately 828,000 square miles from France, doubling its size at that time.
Texas Annexation
Date: December 29, 1845
Texas was annexed into the United States after gaining independence from Mexico.
Oregon Territory
Date: August 14, 1846
The Oregon Treaty established U.S. claims over present-day Oregon, Washington, Idaho, and parts of Montana.
Gadsden Purchase
Date: June 8, 1854
The U.S. purchased land from Mexico that is now southern Arizona and New Mexico.
Significant Wars
American Revolutionary War
Dates: April 19, 1775 – September 3, 1783
This conflict resulted in American independence from British rule.
War of 1812
Dates: June 18, 1812 – February 18, 1815
A conflict between the United States and Great Britain over maritime rights and territorial expansion.
Mexican-American War
Dates: April 25, 1846 – February 2, 1848
This war resulted in significant territorial gains for the U.S., including California and New Mexico.
Civil War
Dates: April 12, 1861 – April 9, 1865
A conflict between Northern states loyal to the Union and Southern states that seceded from it.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This List Contains United States History.
